\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 The last of the students had trickled out, leaving behind the familiar post-club mess\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 dried paint smears on the tables, sponges abandoned in water cups, the scent of turpentine mixed with the sharp smell of acrylics. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Haruki stacked the final canvas board onto the storage shelf, her muscles moving on autopilot after years of this routine.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0  "I swear,\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8221\'94 Aiko groaned, \u8220\'93Those three gremlins are\~}{\f1\fs24\b0\i1 trying}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \~to become abstract artist themselves," she said, gesturing to the dried splatters of cerulean and crimson on the floor where the chaotic trio had been experimenting}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Akihito was already scrubbing at a stubborn oil pastel mark on the table. "At least Kenzo\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s improving," he remarked. "His figure sketches were decent. But the moment he picks up a brush, he didn\u8217\'92t really do good."}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Haruki chuckled, tossing a crumpled paper towel at him. "Be nice. He\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s got the eye for proportions\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 just needs to loosen up." She mimed stiff brushstrokes in the air. "He paints like he\u8217\'92s afraid the paints cost an arm and legs."}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 "Have you seen Naoko\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s painting?" Aiko grinned, propping her chin on her palm. "Her cliffs today looked like they\u8217\'92d survive the apocalypse. But when I asked her to paint a tree next to them it became an Instant lollipop sticks."}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 "Specialization isn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t a bad thing, Aiko." Haruki said, wiping her hands on her already-stained apron. "Maybe we should encourage her to draw more rocks."}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93She need to learn to paint something else, what is she? A rock painter?\u8221\'94 Aiko said}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 But before they could continue, the door creaked open.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Haruki turned, expecting to see a first-year retrieving a forgotten sketchbook. Instead, the silhouette of Mrs. Matsuoka filled the doorway, her face lit by the golden haze of sunset streaming in from the hallway.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Their arts and craft teacher stood with her usual quiet grace, her cardigan sleeves rolled up to the elbows\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 practical, as always. Silver streaked through her otherwise dark hair, and her round glasses caught the light as she smiled. The lines around her eyes deepened with warmth.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 All three students straightened instinctively. "Good evening, Mrs. Matsuoka!" they chorused, bowing in unison.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Mrs. Matsuoka chuckled, stepping inside. "No need for formalities," she said, her voice as soothing as the hum of the old radiator in winter. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 "Fujiyama-san,\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8221\'94 Mrs. Matsuoka said, turning to Haruki, \u8220\'93Could I speak with you in my office?" }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Haruki shot a questioning look at Aiko and Akihito. Aiko waved her off with both hands. "Go, go! We've got this." She dramatically flexed her arms. "These cleaning skills didn't earn me 'Vice President' for nothing."}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Akihito simply nodded, already reorganizing the pigment tubes by color gradient.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 "Right...thanks," Haruki murmured, grabbing her bag. As she followed Mrs. Matsuoka out, the door clicked shut behind them.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 The moment the footsteps faded, Aiko spun to Akihito, eyes sparkling with mischief. She pressed her back against the door and whispered, "Do you think she's finally getting expelled?"}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Akihito didn't look up from his meticulous brush-cleaning. "I'm actually surprised she hasn't been yet."}
